    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available for acquisition is a mechanically sorted 2004 BMW M3 (E46), featuring the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six engine. This power plant utilizes individual throttle bodies and double-VANOS variable valve timing to deliver a broad torque curve and an 8,000 RPM redline. The drivetrain is anchored by a precise Getrag 6-speed manual transmission and a factory-spec limited-slip differential. Critical preventative maintenance has been addressed, including rear subframe reinforcement and a comprehensive valve shim adjustment. The suspension maintains its factory kinematics with refreshed bushings, ensuring the sharp turn-in and tactile feedback characteristic of the chassis. Recent service records indicate a cooling system overhaul and a fresh rod bearing inspection, making this an ideal candidate for the discerning enthusiast seeking a performance-ready driver.",
